<item>
            <title>[PIG-813] Semantics of * and count</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-813</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Continuation of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-812&quot; title=&quot;COUNT(*) does not work &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-812&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-812&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-812&quot; title=&quot;COUNT(*) does not work &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-812&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-812&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for more details.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In order for this to be resolved in the right manner the following must added in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://hadoop.apache.org/pig/docs/r0.2.0/piglatin.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hadoop.apache.org/pig/docs/r0.2.0/piglatin.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) The semantics of * as explained by Olga.&lt;br/&gt;
2) An example of GROUP ALL&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise people will waste their time doing the same (documentation-caused) mistakes again.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
